Sexual heterodonty present; upper anterolateral teeth in an adult male paratype (
MZB 15550
) with enlarged central cusp compared to those in the female paratype ( CSIRO H 5858 –01), teeth height ~ 1.3 vs. 0.6–0.7 mm .

Distribution. Known from the southern coast of Java, and off the islands of Bali and Lombok in eastern Indonesia , and has also been recorded from several landing sites in the Philippines (see
Fig. 9
).
